Major News Items in Leading Philippine Newspapers
MANILA , December 24 ( Xinhua ) -- The following are major news items in leading Philippine newspapers Thursday .
Manila Bulletin :
-- Philippine Central Bank Governor Gabriel Singson said that his country 's year-end inflation rate will be contained at an average of 9.5 percent despite the heightened consumer spending because of the holiday season .
Manila Standard :
-- Philippine President Joseph Estrada fired Customs Commissioner Pedro Mendoza Wednesday after learning that he had sown terror among guests and security personnel of the Manila Hotel by poking a gun at them .
Business World :
-- Philippine business leaders are projecting economic recovery to kick in starting next year with agriculture and industry bouncing back to push gross domestic product to a 2 percent growth rate .
